<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--CSS-->
CSS: Cascading Style Sheets
Cascading: A style applied to a parent element will also apply to all children elements 
           within the parent unless specified
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Using CSS:
1. Inline CSS: Uses style attribute to a single HTML element.
ex: <h1 style="color:blue;">Blue Heading</h1>
2. Internal CSS: Define style in <head> section and within the <style> element for a single HTML page
ex:
<head>
<style>
    body{background-color:powderblue;}
    h1{color:blue;}
</style>
</head>
3. External CSS: Make a style at another file using class
ex:
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CSS Color, Fonts, Border, and Sizes:
ex:
h1{
    color:blue;
    font-family:verdana;
    font-size:300%;
    border:2px solid powderblue;
}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CSS Padding and Margin: Padding is space between text and border, margin is space outside the border.
ex:
p{
    border: 2px solid powderblue;
    padding: 30px;
    margin: 50px;
}
